Pop the #kettle{} onto boil for water to use for the rice. Halve, peel and thinly
slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a
#garlic press{}). Trim the @Green Beans{150%g} then chop into thirds. Drain the
@Smoked Tofu{225%g} then chop into 2cm chunks.

Heat a splash of oil in a #saucepan{} over medium heat. Add the shallot, stir
and cook until softened, ~{3%minutes}. Add the garlic, @North Indian Style Spice
Mix{1%portion} and half the @Nigella Seeds{1%portion}, stir and cook for another
~{1%minute}.

Next add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and stir to coat in the spices. Pour in the
@Water{300%ml} (see ingredients for amount), add the @KNORR Vegetable Stock{1},
stir and cover with a #lid{}. Cook on medium-low heat for ~{5%minutes}, then
remove the lid and quickly put the green beans on top of the rice. Pop the lid
back on, cook for ~{5%minutes} more then remove from the heat. Leave for
~{10%minutes}. The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Meanwhile, chop the @Medium Tomato{2}(chopped into small chunks) and pop into a
#bowl{}. Roughly chop the @Flat Leaf Parsley{1}(chopped roughly, stalks and all)
and halve the @Lemon{1}. Stir half of the parsley into the tomato bowl and
season with @salt{to taste} and a squeeze of lemon juice. Stir in the
@Olive Oil{1%portion} (see ingredients for amount) and keep to one side.

Heat a splash of oil in a #frying pan{} over high heat. When the oil is hot,
add the tofu pieces and stir fry until golden brown and crispy all over,
~{8-10%minutes}, adjusting the heat if necessary. Toss the tofu frequently to
make sure it browns on all sides. When golden, season with salt and squeeze on
the @Mango Chutney{80%g} and stir gently to coat. Sprinkle on the remaining
nigella seeds. Remove from the heat.

Fluff the rice up with a #fork{}. Add the tomato salsa and stir in gently.
Season to taste with salt, @pepper{to taste} and lemon juice. Share the rice
between your #bowls{} and top with the tofu nuggets. Spoon the warm mango
chutney all over and finish with a sprinkle of parsley.